   "info" : "<table width=\"100%\" summary=\"page for Burt\"><tr><td>Burt</td><td style=\"text-align: right;\">R Documentation</td></tr></table>\\n<h2>Fraudulent Data on IQs of Twins Raised Apart</h2>\\n<h3>Description</h3>\\n<p>The <code>Burt</code> data frame has 27 rows and 4 columns.\\nThe &ldquo;data&rdquo; were simply (and notoriously) manufactured.  The\\nsame data are in the dataset &ldquo;twins&quot; in the <code>alr3</code>\\npackage, but with different labels.\\n</p>\\n<h3>Usage</h3>\\n<pre>\\nBurt\\n</pre>\\n<h3>Format</h3>\\n<p>This data frame contains the following columns:\\n</p>\\n<dl>\\n<dt>IQbio</dt><dd>\\n<p>IQ of twin raised by biological parents\\n</p>\\n</dd>\\n<dt>IQfoster</dt><dd>\\n<p>IQ of twin raised by foster parents\\n</p>\\n</dd>\\n<dt>class</dt><dd>\\n<p>A factor with levels (note: out of order):\\n<code>high</code>;\\n<code>low</code>;\\n<code>medium</code>.\\n</p>\\n</dd>\\n</dl>\\n<h3>Source</h3>\\n<p>Burt, C. (1966) \\nThe genetic determination of differences in intelligence: \\nA study of monozygotic twins reared together and apart. \\n<em>British Journal of Psychology</em> <b>57</b>, 137&ndash;153.\\n</p>\\n",
